:"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Baroness Alice was born about 1207, in Kent, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Hamo de Crevequer de Crèvecœur Baron of Chatham Baron of Chatham."},"et":{"about 1207–":"umbes 1207–Surnud","1210–1263":"1210–1263","1223–1263":"1223–1263","1224–1263":"1224–1263","1226–Female":"1226–Surnud","1263–1263":"1263–1263","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","abt 1226":"umbes 1226","1226":"1226","1224":"1224","about 1207":"umbes 1207","1223 (age 40 1263)":"8. jaanuar 1223 kuni 7. jaanuar 1224","1223":"1223","1210":"1210","ABT 1224":"umbes 1224","1263":"1263","1233 (age 30 1263)":"1263","1207":"1207","of Kent, Eng.":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chatam,Kent,England":"Chatham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Kent Co., Eng.":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chatham,Kent,England":"Chatham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",",Kent,England.":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1207–":"noin 1207–Kuollut","1210–1263":"1210–1263","1223–1263":"1223–1263","1224–1263":"1224–1263","1226–Female":"1226–Kuollut","1263–1263":"1263–1263","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","abt 1226":"noin 1226","1226":"1226","1224":"1224","ab